9 Months</div></div><div
class="how-to-desc"><div
class="how-to-image">
<picture>
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-completed-800x800-20200820.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="250" height="250" alt="How to Start a Nonprofit Organization:">
</picture></div><p>A step-by-step guide to starting your very own nonprofit organization.</p></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=decide-which-type-of-nonprofit-you-would-like-to-open>Decide which type of nonprofit you would like to open.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ensure-that-you-have-sufficient-evidence-that-your-npo-will-positively-contribute-to-this-unmet-issue-or-need>Ensure that you have sufficient evidence that your NPO will positively contribute to this unmet issue or need.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-look-at-local-statistics-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-055422_phtk.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ensure that you have sufficient evidence that your NPO will positively contribute to this unmet issue or need."></div></div><p>You will find it easier to get donations and receive grants if you have solid evidence that your NPO will serve a practical purpose. Your research must include statistics and numbers that back up your idea.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ensure-that-there-are-no-existing-organizations-that-are-currently-serving-the-same-issue-or-need>Ensure that there are no existing organizations that are currently serving the same issue or need.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-find-your-state-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ensure that there are no existing organizations that are currently serving the same issue or need."></div></div><p>Your NPO should serve an issue or need that has not already been identified or serviced. The National Council of Nonprofits has a <a
href="https://www.councilofnonprofits.org/">handy tool</a> that helps you identify the existing NPOs in your area. Use the tool to ensure that your nonprofit idea is unique.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section1-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=think-about-the-type-of-people-you-want-to-attract-to-support-your-organization>Think about the type of people you want to attract to support your organization.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-name-a-fashion-brand-288x288-20200622-13.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Think about the type of people you want to attract to support your organization."></div></div><p>It is crucial to gain the right type of support for your NPO to ensure the success of your organization. Understanding your target demographic will make it easier for you to gain supporters and members.</p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>It is critical to develop a mission statement that clearly outlines your nonprofit's purpose, its target group, and how your organization will contribute to this issue or need. Your mission statement does not have to be lengthy or explain the details of your NPO and its work. It should be to the point and must, very succinctly, define who you are, what your goal is, and your motivation for achieving this goal.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=write-a-business-plan>Write a business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-executive-summary>Create a executive summary.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-an-executive-summary-288x288-20200727_2023-09-26-055704_yhfn.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a executive summary."></div></div><p>This should be a synopsis of your business plan.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-company-overview-and-description>Create a company overview and description.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-a-business-description-288x288-20200729.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a company overview and description."></div></div><p>List details of your organization, its foundations, and mission.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=write-a-market-analysis>Write a market analysis.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-a-market-analysis-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Write a market analysis."></div></div><p>Explanation of your target group, your stakeholders and SWOT analysis.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=describe-your-products-and-services>Describe your products and services.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-think-about-the-products-you-will-sell-288x288-20200710.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Describe your products and services."></div></div><p>Details of what makes your nonprofit unique and how your organization will add value by addressing a relevant need.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-marketing-plan>Create a marketing plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-marketing-plan-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a marketing plan."></div></div><p>Explanation of who your organization will service, how you will locate this target group, and how you will convince people to support your cause.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-an-operational-plan>Create an operational plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-set-up-a-separate-private-home-office-if-working-from-home-288x288-20200723_2023-09-26-060124_poqi.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create an operational plan."></div></div><p>Details of your office location, supplies, and equipment required, how you plan to deliver your service/s, and what type of staff and volunteers you require.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=detail-your-organizational-structure>Detail your organizational structure.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-list-your-essential-staff-288x288-20200812.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Detail your organizational structure."></div></div><p>A list of your staff with details of their roles and how they are organized.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section2-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=create-a-financial-plan>Create a financial plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-detailed-financial-plan-288x288-20200811_2023-09-26-060326_nnue.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Create a financial plan."></div></div><p>Details of cash flow analysis, projected budgets, and revenue generation. This section will help you to apply for grants and loans, and will be of most interest to potential investors.</p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Many founders neglect to develop a proper business plan for their nonprofit as they have the misconception that business plans only apply to “for-profit” organizations. It is vital to create a detailed business plan before incorporating your NPO as this will enhance your funding opportunities with investors, donors, and board members.</p></div><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Use our handy business plan template to get you up and running.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=generate-revenue-for-your-nonprofit>Generate revenue for your nonprofit.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=explore-multiple-avenues>Explore multiple avenues.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-explore-multiple-avenues-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Explore multiple avenues."></div></div><p>While most “for-profit” organizations make their revenue primarily from products and services, nonprofit organizations have many avenues through which they can generate revenue.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>It is wise to develop separate strategies when approaching each revenue source as each of these has dynamic characteristics.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-fees-for-services-and-products>Obtain fees for services and products.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-look-into-fees-288x288-20200723_2023-09-26-060518_ztwy.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain fees for services and products."></div></div><p>This is revenue generated from services and products and includes money received from membership dues, event tickets, professional services and products e.g., merchandise.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=source-private-contributions>Source private contributions.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-source-private-contributions-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Source private contributions."></div></div><p>This consists of donations received and can be solicited through individual donors, fundraising activities and sponsorship.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>You must complete the <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/charitable-organizations/charitable-solicitation-initial-state-registration">Charitable Solicitation Registration</a> via the IRS website before you can accept any donations or engage in fundraising activities.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>For more information on your state’s regulations, you can select your state from this <a
href="https://www.fundraisingregistration.com/resources/states-requiring-registration-map.php">interactive map</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=source-government-grants>Source government grants.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-get-funding-from-angel-investors-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Source government grants."></div></div><p>This is funding provided by the government to organizations and institutions whose mission and projects benefit specific parts of the population or a whole community. The federal government offers guidance for those that wish to apply for a grant at <a
href="https://www.usa.gov/grants">www.usa.gov/grants</a>. Once you have sufficient information and meet the eligibility criteria, you can apply for a government grant at <a
href="https://www.grants.gov/web/grants/home.html">www.grants.gov/web/grants/home</a>. Only apply for a grant through official government channels.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Beware of government grant scams. The Federal Trade Commission warns of many government grant scams that attract organizations through advertisements in local newspapers, magazines, online and over the phone. You can get more information about government grant scams <a
href="https://consumer.ftc.gov/articles/government-grant-scams">here</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=approach-these-reputable-sources-of-grants-for-nonprofits>Approach these reputable sources of grants for nonprofits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-obtain-funding-288x288-20200728.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Approach these reputable sources of grants for nonprofits."></div></div><ul><li><p><a
href="https://www.grants.gov/">Grants.gov</a>.</p></li><li><p><a
href="https://www.neh.gov/">National Endowment for the Humanities</a>.</p></li><li><p><a
href="https://www.arts.gov/">National Endowment for the Arts</a>.</p></li><li><p><a
href="https://www.puffinfoundation.org/">The Puffin Foundation</a>.</p></li></ul></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=choose-a-name-for-your-nonprofit-organization>Choose a name for your nonprofit organization.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-memorable-name>Choose a memorable name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-write-down-name-ideas-288x288-20200814_2023-09-26-060924_cvsh.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a memorable name."></div></div><p>When deciding on a name for your NPO, the name that you choose must be easy to remember, appealing, aligned with your service and mission statement, and have a positive tone.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=brainstorm-ideas>Brainstorm ideas.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-name-a-farm-business-3.2-288x288-20200622.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Brainstorm ideas."></div></div><p>Think of the many names that you like for your organization and trim the list to the three that best fit the characteristics above.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=check-name-availability>Check name availability.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-name-a-charity-7.3-288x288-20200618.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Check name availability."></div></div><p>You can check if the name that you have chosen is available through your state's secretary of state website. You also need to check that your name has not been trademarked at the <a
href="https://www.uspto.gov/">United States Patent and Trademark Office</a>.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=check-domain-availability>Check domain availability.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-name-a-shoe-company-288x288-20200623-19.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Check domain availability."></div></div><p>You can conduct preliminary checks to ensure that the website domain and social media accounts are available. If your domain is taken, you could add your state’s name to the domain, if you really want that name. Bear in mind that nonprofit domains typically end with <strong>.org</strong>.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=conduct-an-independent-name-search>Conduct an independent name search.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-check-the-names-on-google-288x288-20200703.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Conduct an independent name search."></div></div><p>You can conduct some independent research to check if the proposed name or a similar name is currently in use. Some names are in use even though they are not on file with the Secretary of State.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section4-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=reserve-your-corporate-name>Reserve your corporate name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-check-with-the-secretary-of-state-288x288-20200619.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Reserve your corporate name."></div></div><p>You can apply for name reservation through your state's Secretary of State’s website.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=recruit-your-board>Recruit your board.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=check-your-state-requirements>Check your state requirements.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-the-state-database-288x288-20200619.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Check your state requirements."></div></div><p>Most states require that you establish your board before incorporating your organization. Even if your particular state doesn’t require board members when incorporating, it is a great idea to recruit your board prior to incorporation as this will make the process easier and will be beneficial when you are faced with the initial challenges of starting a nonprofit organization.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section5-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=recruit-board-members-who-are-motivated-and-supportive>Recruit board members who are motivated and supportive.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-recruit-board-members-who-are-motivated-and-supportive-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Recruit board members who are motivated and supportive."></div></div><p>You should recruit board members who possess the right blend of skills, credentials and experience to ensure the healthy growth of your NPO.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section5-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=ensure-that-these-essential-roles-are-filled-first>Ensure that these essential roles are filled first.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-ensure-that-these-essential-roles-are-filled-first-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Ensure that these essential roles are filled first."></div></div><ul><li>Chairperson.</li><li>Vice-Chairperson.</li><li>Secretary.</li><li>Treasurer.</li></ul><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Essential character traits of successful board members at nonprofit organizations include a strong work ethic, dependability, a positive attitude, self-motivation, a team-oriented approach, effective communication, and adaptability.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section6" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>6.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=incorporate-your-nonprofit-organization>Incorporate your nonprofit organization.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section6-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=file-your-incorporation-paperwork>File your incorporation paperwork.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-by-organizer-incorporator-288x288-20200618.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="File your incorporation paperwork."></div></div><p>By this point, you've already decided on a business name, appointed board members, and chosen a legal structure. Now it's time to file your incorporation paperwork. You will need to formally file paperwork (articles of incorporation) and pay the relevant filing fees to your Secretary of State. Regulations for each state differ so be sure to confirm your requirements with your Secretary of State’s website or the <a
href="https://www.nasconet.org/">National Association of State Charity Officials (NASCO)</a>. If you intend on soliciting donations in multiple states, you will need to register your intentions with NASCO.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section6-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>6.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=obtain-licenses-and-permits>Obtain licenses and permits.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-license-and-permits-288x288-20200729_2023-09-26-062149_blkh.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Obtain licenses and permits."></div></div><p>You will need to check if your NPO requires any licenses and/or permits. The U.S. Small Business Administration has <a
href="https://www.sba.gov/business-guide/launch-your-business/apply-licenses-permits">detailed information available</a> that you can use to guide you.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>7.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=register-for-your-nonprofit-organization-to-be-tax-exempt>Register for your nonprofit organization to be tax-exempt.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=go-to-the-irs-website>Go to the IRS website.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-go-to-the-irs-website-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Go to the IRS website."></div></div><p>Your nonprofit organization may be eligible for federal income tax exemption. The IRS website offers detailed instructions on <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/charitable-organizations/state-charity-offices">how to apply for tax exemptions</a>. The IRS also provides a <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/p557.pdf">comprehensive guide to tax exemptions for nonprofit organizations</a>.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Section 501 of the Internal Revenue Code (IRC) explains which types of nonprofit organizations are tax-exempt. Under Section 501(c) of the IRC, there are many types of <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/types-of-tax-exempt-organizations">nonprofit organizations that can file for tax exemptions</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-with-the-irs>Register with the IRS.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-with-the-irs-288x288-20200922.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register with the IRS."></div></div><p>You will need to register with the IRS as your appropriate 501(c) organization in order to receive tax exemptions. You can access the IRS Tax Exemption application <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/application-process">here</a>. The IRS charges filing fees to apply for a nonprofit tax exemption status which can be anywhere between $400 to $850. You can find more information <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/form-1023-and-1023-ez-amount-of-user-fee">here</a>. The IRS tax exemption application process can take between 3 to 12 months.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-with-your-state>Register with your state.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-the-state-database-288x288-20200619_2023-09-26-062448_urob.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register with your state."></div></div><p>Once you have received your tax-exempt status, you will need to register your nonprofit with the state that you are located in. The IRS website can <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/charities-non-profits/state-links">direct you to your state</a> where you can find the correct office, view filing procedures, and confirm annual reporting requirements.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>7.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=fill-out-an-irs-form-990>Fill out an IRS Form 990.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-fill-out-an-irs-form-990-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Fill out an IRS Form 990."></div></div><p>The IRS requires that you fill out an <a
href="https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-990">IRS Form 990</a>, which is the annual financial and informational return filed by all tax-exempt nonprofit and charitable organizations. The IRS uses this form to gather information about your NPO and ensure that you are compliant. The IRS Form 990 must be filed by the 15th day of the 5th month following the organization’s tax year end date.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>8.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=identify-premises-for-your-nonprofit-organizations-headquarters>Identify premises for your nonprofit organization’s headquarters.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=determine-if-you-need-an-office>Determine if you need an office.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rent-a-virtual-office-space-288x288-20200727.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Determine if you need an office."></div></div><p>If funds are really tight, you can choose to run your NPO without a physical office, as some NPOs are run from home. You will, however, need a P.O. box to accept mail and this may cost anywhere between $50 to $1,000, depending on your location and the size that you need.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=focus-on-cutting-costs>Focus on cutting costs.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-shared-office-space-names-2400x2400-2020083.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Focus on cutting costs."></div></div><p>If you do want to rent office space, it is advisable to keep it as simple as possible. You may consider getting as few desks as necessary, a phone, a laptop, a printer, and a filing cabinet. You can contact <a
href="https://www.nonprofitcenters.org/">The Nonprofit Centers</a> or the <a
href="https://www.councilofnonprofits.org/">National Council of Nonprofits</a> for inexpensive office space options.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=these-organizations-donate-essential-furniture-and-computer-equipment-to-nPOs>These organizations donate essential furniture and computer equipment to NPOs.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-check-out-these-organizations-that-donate-essential-furniture-and-computer-equipment-to-nonprofit-organizations-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="These organizations donate essential furniture and computer equipment to NPOs."></div></div><ul><li><a
href="https://greenstandards.com/for-nonprofits/">GreenStandards</a>.</li><li><a
href="https://www.csr-eco-solutions.com/index.html">CSR Eco Solutions</a>.</li><li><a
href="https://www.freecycle.org/">FreeCycle.org</a>.</li><li><a
href="https://interconnection.org/computergrants.php">Interconnection.org</a>.</li><li><a
href="https://www.computerswithcauses.org/application/">Computer With Causes</a>.</li></ul></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section9" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>9.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=recruit-staff>Recruit Staff.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section9-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pace-your-recruitment>Pace your recruitment.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-hire-employees-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-063712_uwlh.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pace your recruitment."></div></div><p>While some nonprofit organizations are run solely by the founder, many organizations choose to recruit at least one staff member and/or volunteer until such time that they feel the need to recruit more.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>It is recommended to reach out to other nonprofit organizations of a similar size to get advice on the number of staff that you might need.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section9-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=hire-key-positions-first>Hire key positions first.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-hire-a-trademark-attorney-288x288-20200811.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Hire key positions first."></div></div><ul><li>General Administrator.</li><li>Membership Manager/Coordinator.</li><li>Media &amp; Communications Manager/Officer.</li><li>Fundraising &amp; Events Manager/Coordinator.</li></ul><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p><strong>Don’t rush the recruitment process</strong> and don’t settle for applicants who do not fully meet your criteria. It is advisable to recruit multi-skilled applicants who could serve multiple roles in your nonprofit organization. Consider using a staffing agency to help you with the process.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>10.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=set-up-your-website-and-social-media-accounts>Set up your website and social media accounts.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=put-thought-into-your-design>Put thought into your design.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-website-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-063851_ktvu.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Put thought into your design."></div></div><p>A well-designed website can do wonders for your NPO. You could attract the right attention, your work could be more easily promoted, and you could build trust with your target audience, giving you a better opportunity to make a greater impact.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Your website will prove to be invaluable as it will help you raise money, coordinate events, attract volunteers, and share success stories.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=have-a-detailed-home-page>Have a detailed home page.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-build-a-website-288x288-20200817_2023-09-26-063934_knih.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Have a detailed home page."></div></div><p>This is visually appealing and must encourage visitors to join your NPO or donate, and should include recent news, featured members, and upcoming events.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-an-about-us-page>Include an About Us page.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-update-your-website-288x288-20200703.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include an About Us page."></div></div><p>This page can include your mission, vision, history, staff, and general information about your organization.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step4" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.4&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-a-join-us-page>Include a Join Us page.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-website-288x288-20200718_2023-09-26-064104_nkdm.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include a Join Us page."></div></div><p>This page must give potential new members all the information they need to know before joining your organization and should have a membership form to join online.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step5" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.5&nbsp;</span><h4 id=make-your-donate-button-stand-out>Make your Donate button stand out.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-make-your-donate-button-stand-out-288x288-20200922.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Make your Donate button stand out."></div></div><p>This button must lead to a page that gives potential donors all the information they need to know before donating to your organization, and should have a membership form to donate online.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-an-events-page>Include an Events page.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-include-an-events-page-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include an Events page."></div></div><p>This page should display your upcoming events and should include invitations for interested people to attend and register. You should also list the benefits of joining your organization here. This page is usually structured in a calendar format.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step7" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.7&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-a-news-or-blog-section>Include a News or Blog section.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-include-a-news-or-blog-section-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include a News or Blog section."></div></div><p>This page should have the latest news about your organization and its work, and should have relevant blog posts.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step8" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.8&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-a-resources-page>Include a Resources page.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-include-a-resources-page-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include a Resources page."></div></div><p>This page should include resources that your organization publishes, if applicable.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step9" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.9&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-a-members-only-section>Include a Members-Only Section.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-include-a-member-only-section-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include a Members-Only Section."></div></div><p>This page is usually restricted to members of your organization only and can be accessed through member login credentials.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step10" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>10.10&nbsp;</span><h4 id=include-a-contact-us-page>Include a Contact Us page.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-include-a-contact-us-page-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Include a Contact Us page."></div></div><p>This page will include all contact information for your organization.</p><div
class="step-direction tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
