-060518_ztwy.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Source private contributions.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This consists of donations received and can be solicited through individual donors, fundraising activities and sponsorship.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section3-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-source-private-contributions-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>You must complete the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/charities-non-profits\/charitable-organizations\/charitable-solicitation-initial-state-registration\">Charitable Solicitation Registration<\/a> via the IRS website before you can accept any donations or engage in fundraising activities.<\/p>\n"},{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>For more information on your state\u2019s regulations, you can select your state from this <a href=\"https:\/\/www.fundraisingregistration.com\/resources\/states-requiring-registration-map.php\">interactive map<\/a>.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Source government grants.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This is funding provided by the government to organizations and institutions whose mission and projects benefit specific parts of the population or a whole community. The federal government offers guidance for those that wish to apply for a grant at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.usa.gov\/grants\">www.usa.gov\/grants<\/a>. Once you have sufficient information and meet the eligibility criteria, you can apply for a government grant at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.grants.gov\/web\/grants\/home.html\">www.grants.gov\/web\/grants\/home<\/a>. Only apply for a grant through official government channels.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#h