perwork. You will need to formally file paperwork (articles of incorporation) and pay the relevant filing fees to your Secretary of State. Regulations for each state differ so be sure to confirm your requirements with your Secretary of State\u2019s website or the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.nasconet.org\/\">National Association of State Charity Officials (NASCO)<\/a>. If you intend on soliciting donations in multiple states, you will need to register your intentions with NASCO.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section6-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-by-organizer-incorporator-288x288-20200618.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Obtain licenses and permits.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>You will need to check if your NPO requires any licenses and\/or permits. The U.S. Small Business Administration has <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sba.gov\/business-guide\/launch-your-business\/apply-licenses-permits\">detailed information available<\/a> that you can use to guide you.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section6-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-license-and-permits-288x288-20200729_2023-09-26-062149_blkh.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"7","name":"<p>Register for your nonprofit organization to be tax-exempt.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Go to the IRS website.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Your nonprofit organization may be eligible for federal income tax exemption. The IRS website offers detailed instructions on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/charities-non-profits\/charitable-organizations\/state-charity-offices\">how to apply for tax exemptions<\/a>. The IRS also provides a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/pub\/irs-pdf\/p557.pdf\">comprehensive guide to tax exemptions for nonprofit organizations<\/a>.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-go-to-the-irs-website-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Section 501 of the Internal Revenue Code (IRC) explains which types of nonprofit organizations are tax-exempt. Under Section 501(c) of the IRC, there are many types of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/charities-non-profits\/types-of-tax-exempt-organizations\">nonprofit organizations that can file for tax exemptions<\/a>.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Register with the IRS.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>You will need to register with the IRS as your appropriate 501(c) organization in order to receive tax exemptions. You can access the IRS Tax Exemption application <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/charities-non-profits\/application-process\">here<\/a>. The IRS charges filing fees to apply for a nonprofit tax exemption status which can be anywhere between $400 to $850. You can find more information <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/charities-non-profits\/form-1023-and-1023-ez-amount-of-user-fee\">here<\/a>. The IRS tax exemption application process can take between 3 to 12 months.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-with-the-irs-288x288-20200922.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Register with your state.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>Once you have received your tax-exempt status, you will need to register your nonprofit with the state that you are located in. The IRS website can <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/charities-non-profits\/state-links\">direct you to your state<\/a> where you can find the correct office, view filing procedures, and confirm annual reporting requirements.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-search-the-state-database-288x288-20200619_2023-09-26-062448_urob.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Fill out an IRS Form 990.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The IRS requires that you fill out an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.irs.gov\/forms-pubs\/about-form-990\">IRS Form 990<\/a>, which is the annual financial and informational return filed by all tax-exempt nonprofit and charitable organizations. The IRS uses this form to gather information about your NPO and ensure that you are compliant. The IRS Form 990 must be filed by the 15th day of the 5th month following the organization\u2019s tax year end date.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section7-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-fill-out-an-irs-form-990-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"8","name":"<p>Identify premises for your nonprofit organization\u2019s headquarters.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Determine if you need an office.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If funds are really tight, you can choose to run your NPO without a physical office, as some NPOs are run from home. You will, however, need a P.O. box to accept mail and this may cost anywhere between $50 to $1,000, depending on your location and the size that you need.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-rent-a-virtual-office-space-288x288-20200727.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Focus on cutting costs.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>If you do want to rent office space, it is advisable to keep it as simple as possible. You may consider getting as few desks as necessary, a phone, a laptop, a printer, and a filing cabinet. You can contact <a href=\"https:\/\/www.nonprofitcenters.org\/\">The Nonprofit Centers<\/a> or the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.councilofnonprofits.org\/\">National Council of Nonprofits<\/a> for inexpensive office space options.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-shared-office-space-names-2400x2400-2020083.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"2400","width":"2400"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>These organizations donate essential furniture and computer equipment to NPOs.<\/p>\n","text":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/greenstandards.com\/for-nonprofits\/\">GreenStandards<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.csr-eco-solutions.com\/index.html\">CSR Eco Solutions<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.freecycle.org\/\">FreeCycle.org<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/interconnection.org\/computergrants.php\">Interconnection.org<\/a>.<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.computerswithcauses.org\/application\/\">Computer With Causes<\/a>.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section8-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-check-out-these-organizations-that-donate-essential-furniture-and-computer-equipment-to-nonprofit-organizations-288x288-20200817.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"9","name":"<p>Recruit Staff.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Pace your recruitment.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>While some nonprofit organizations are run solely by the founder, many organizations choose to recruit at least one staff member and\/or volunteer until such time that they feel the need to recruit more.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section9-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-hire-employees-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-063712_uwlh.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>It is recommended to reach out to other nonprofit organizations of a similar size to get advice on the number of staff that you might need.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Hire key positions first.<\/p>\n","text":"<ul>\n<li>General Administrator.<\/li>\n<li>Membership Manager\/Coordinator.<\/li>\n<li>Media &amp; Communications Manager\/Officer.<\/li>\n<li>Fundraising &amp; Events Manager\/Coordinator.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section9-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-hire-a-trademark-attorney-288x288-20200811.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p><strong>Don\u2019t rush the recruitment process<\/strong> and don\u2019t settle for applicants who do not fully meet your criteria. It is advisable to recruit multi-skilled applicants who could serve multiple roles in your nonprofit organization. Consider using a staffing agency to help you with the process.<\/p>\n"}]}]},{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"10","name":"<p>Set up your website and social media accounts.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Put thought into your design.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>A well-designed website can do wonders for your NPO. You could attract the right attention, your work could be more easily promoted, and you could build trust with your target audience, giving you a better opportunity to make a greater impact.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step1","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-website-288x288-20200728_2023-09-26-063851_ktvu.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"},"itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToTip","text":"<p>Your website will prove to be invaluable as it will help you raise money, coordinate events, attract volunteers, and share success stories.<\/p>\n"}]},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"2","name":"<p>Have a detailed home page.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This is visually appealing and must encourage visitors to join your NPO or donate, and should include recent news, featured members, and upcoming events.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step2","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-build-a-website-288x288-20200817_2023-09-26-063934_knih.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"3","name":"<p>Include an About Us page.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This page can include your mission, vision, history, staff, and general information about your organization.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step3","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-update-your-website-288x288-20200703.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"4","name":"<p>Include a Join Us page.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This page must give potential new members all the information they need to know before joining your organization and should have a membership form to join online.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step4","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-create-a-website-288x288-20200718_2023-09-26-064104_nkdm.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"5","name":"<p>Make your Donate button stand out.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This button must lead to a page that gives potential donors all the information they need to know before donating to your organization, and should have a membership form to donate online.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step5","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-make-your-donate-button-stand-out-288x288-20200922.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2","height":"288","width":"288"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"6","name":"<p>Include an Events page.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>This page should display your upcoming events and should include invitations for interested people to attend and register. You should also list the benefits of joining your organization here. This page is usually structured in a calendar format.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization#how-to-start-a-nonprofit-organization-section10-step6","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-include-an-events-page-288x288-20200818.jpeg?c